# AI Developer Rules (CRITICAL)
- Refer to and strictly follow the **Core AI Developer Standard** defined in `.agents/skills/ai_standard_en.md` (English) and `.agents/skills/ai_standard_vi.md` (Vietnamese). You MUST strictly adhere to the **Core Programming Rules (Section 7)**, the **Feature Discovery Protocol (Section 3)**, and the **Feature Development Lifecycle & Progress Tracking (Section 4)**.
- Since this is a Web/App project, refer to and follow the **Web & App Extensions** defined in `.agents/skills/web_app_standard_en.md` and `.agents/skills/web_app_standard_vi.md`.
- BEFORE starting any task or refactoring, you MUST read the project's `docs/overview.md` (or equivalent master document). Look up the target module in the **Core Module Registry** to find its specific code entries and documentation spec.
- You MUST create and maintain `task.md` (using `[ ]`/`[/]`/`[x]`) to track real-time progress and generate `walkthrough.md` with links to source code upon task completion.
- Keep all source code files under a strict budget of **300 lines of code** per file. Decompose large modules, components, classes, and hooks immediately if they approach this limit.
- Document system flow using Mermaid diagrams inside specifications.
- Follow the 4-step workflow: Context Absorption -> Modular Decomposition -> Standard-Compliant Execution -> Alignment & Documentation Update.

## Architecture: Facade + Service Layer Pattern
- ALL HTTP requests MUST go through `shared/services/api.js`. NEVER call `fetch()` directly in Components.
- ALL authentication token access MUST use `AuthHelper.getToken()` from `shared/services/AuthHelper.js`. NEVER use `localStorage.getItem('vuFamilyAuth')` directly.
- ALL analytics events MUST go through `TrackingHelper.TrackingEvent()` from `shared/services/TrackingHelper.js`. NEVER call Firebase Analytics directly.
- ALL UI text strings MUST use `t('key')` from `useTranslation()` hook. NEVER hardcode Vietnamese or English text in JSX.
- ALL config values MUST be read via `ConfigAPI.getString/getNumber/getBoolean/getJSON` from `config.js`.

## Import Rules (CRITICAL — Missing imports cause Runtime Crashes)
- When using `AuthHelper.*`, MUST import: `import { AuthHelper } from '../../shared/services/AuthHelper';`
- When using `TrackingHelper.*`, MUST import: `import { TrackingHelper } from '../../shared/services/TrackingHelper';`
- When using `t()`, MUST import: `import { useTranslation } from '../../shared/hooks/useTranslation';`
- When using `ConfigAPI.*`, MUST import: `import { ConfigAPI } from '../../config.js';`

## Logging
- Use `myLog()`, `myError()`, `myWarning()` from `shared/utils/logger.js`. NEVER use raw `console.log`.

## CSS
- Use CSS variables from theme files: `var(--primary)`, `var(--bg-card)`, etc. NEVER hardcode hex colors.

## Naming Conventions
- Variables/Functions: camelCase
- React Components: PascalCase
- CSS classes: kebab-case
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
- i18n keys: dot.notation (e.g., `login.username`)

## Adding New Features
1. Create folder in `features/`
2. Add API methods to `shared/services/api.js`
3. Add i18n keys to `shared/services/i18n.js` (both `vi` and `en`)
4. Add tracking events to `shared/services/TrackingHelper.js`
5. Add feature flag to `config.js`: `feature_xxx_enabled: true`
6. Register in `App.jsx` and `Sidebar.jsx`

## Server API Response Format
All endpoints MUST return: `{ success: boolean, data: any, message: string, error: string }`
